Title : Faryad Shiri
Text : '''Faryad Shiri''' (in Kurdish: فەریاد شیری) is a contemporary Iranian [[Kurdish people|Kurdish]]<ref>{{cite web | title = Study of creativity in Iran Contemporary Poetry: Title Page | url = http://ac.els-cdn.com/S1877042813029959/1-s2.0-S1877042813029959-main.pdf?_tid=038e5fe8-d2c8-11e3-be1d-00000aacb35f&acdnat=1399124404_452f8e7ea6e0c900393f07d9325819a5}}</ref> poet, critic, writer and translator. He works on [[Kurdish literature|Kurdish]] and [[Persian literature]]. Faryad was born in [[Sahneh]] in 1971. He has published more than twenty works consisting of his poems, translations and stories. He also has received several awards such as Iran poetry prize (2002).<ref>{{cite web | title = Study of creativity in Iran Contemporary Poetry: Title Page | url = http://ac.els-cdn.com/S1877042813029959/1-s2.0-S1877042813029959-main.pdf?_tid=038e5fe8-d2c8-11e3-be1d-00000aacb35f&acdnat=1399124404_452f8e7ea6e0c900393f07d9325819a5}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ibna.ir/fa/doc/naghli/132649|title=Iran's Book News Agency: Faryad Shiri's new book is published|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ibna.ir/fa/doc/naghli/132649|title=IBNA:Iran Book News Agency|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>

==works==
Here is some of his works in poetry and translation:

==Translations==
*Passport of smile and wish (translation of modern Kurdish poetry), Mina, 2002.
*Love songs of chestnuts lands (translation of modern love songs of Kurdish poetry), Meshki, 2009
*A lady whispered Love, Markaz, 2008
*100 Sia Cahamana (Horami poetry), Meshki, 2007 <ref>{{cite web | title = Public Republic, Faryad Shiri: Title Page | url = http://www.public-republic.net/authors/faryad-shiri/}}</ref>

==writings==
*Crows don’t understand sparrows (poetry collection) Dastan Publishing house, 1998.
*My hug is full of journey (poetry collection), Nimnegah, 2003.
*Black people, white people,Negima, 2003.
*Crazy reading of rain (poetry collection in Kurdish language), Shola, 2005.
*Kalamatarh, Morvarid, 2010
*This name needs a new signature, Morvarid, 2010.
*We were lost in the picture on the rain" (story-photo collection), Negima, 2000.
*Homeland is not for sale (poetry collection), Negah, 2012.
*I am lonelier than moon (poetry collection of Kurdish language), Dastan publishing house, 2012.

